label.value: Extended Release Fiber Dosage Form

value.value: A solid in the shape of a slender, elongated thread that is designed to release active and/or inert ingredient(s) at a controlled, prolonged rate so as to reduce dosing frequency.

label.value: Dosage Form for Solution

value.value: A substance intended for administration as a solution.

label.value: Dosage Form for Suspension

value.value: A substance intended for administration as a suspension.

label.value: Extended Release Dosage Form for Suspension

value.value: A substance that forms a suspension upon reconstitution and designed to release active and/or inert ingredient(s) at a controlled, prolonged rate so as to reduce dosing frequency.

label.value: Corneal Squamous Intraepithelial Neoplasia

value.value: A precancerous neoplastic intraepithelial process involving the corneal epithelium.

label.value: Metered Gel Dosage Form

value.value: A gel contained in a device with valves that permits the release of a uniform dose of gel that composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s) upon activation.

label.value: Liposomal Injection Dosage Form

value.value: A substance composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s) encapsulated in liposomes and intended for injection.

label.value: Doxorubicin/Tariquidar
Insert Dosage Form

value.value: A solid or semi-solid intended for administration within the body.

label.value: Extended Release Liquid Dosage Form

value.value: A solution or suspension that is designed to release active and/or inert ingredient(s) at a controlled, prolonged rate so as to reduce dosing frequency.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer TNM Finding v6
Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v6
Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6
Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Low Grade Corneal Squamous Intraepithelial Neoplasia

value.value: A precancerous neoplastic intraepithelial process with low-grade dysplastic features involving the corneal epithelium.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ, also known as grade III pancreatic intraepithelial neoplasia (PanIn III). (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor confined to the pancreas and 2 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor confined to the pancreas but more than 2 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer extending beyond the pancreas, but without involvement of the celiac axis or superior mesenteric artery. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer extending beyond the pancreas, involving the celiac axis or superior mesenteric artery and therefore unresectable. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with no evidence of regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Orbit Sarcoma

value.value: A malignant soft tissue neoplasm that arises from the structures of the orbit.  The majority of the cases are rhabdomyosarcomas.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pN1a TNM Finding

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with metastasis to a single regional lymph node. (from CAP Cancer of the Endocrine Pancreas Protocol- January 2005 Revision)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pN1b TNM Finding

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with metastasis to more than one regional lymph node. (from CAP Cancer of the Endocrine Pancreas Protocol- January 2005 Revision)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with no evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Augmented Lotion Dosage Form

value.value: A lotion that is modified to enhance the release of active and/or inert ingredient(s).

label.value: Lotion Shampoo Dosage Form

value.value: A lotion composed of anionic surfactant intended for administration to the hair or scalp.

label.value: Lung Cancer TNM Finding v6

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Lung Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Lung Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lung cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed, or in which the diagnosis is confirmed by the presence of malignant cells in sputum or bronchial washings, but not visualized by imaging or bronchoscopy. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lung cancer without any evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lung cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor size of 3 cm or less in greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura and without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (not invading the main bronchus). The uncommon superficial tumor of any size with its invasive component limited to the bronchial wall, which may extend proximal to the main bronchus, is also classified as T1. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor size of greater than 3 cm in greatest dimension, or a tumor of any size extending into the main bronchus (2 cm or more distal to the carina), or a tumor of any size invading the visceral pleura, or a tumor with atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis extending to the hilar region without involving the entire lung. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Low Grade Conjunctival Squamous Intraepithelial Neoplasia

value.value: A precancerous neoplastic intraepithelial process with low-grade dysplastic features involving the conjunctival epithelium.

label.value: Lung Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Lung cancer directly invading the chest wall (including superior sulcus tumors), diaphragm, mediastinal pleura or parietal pericardium, or a tumor of any size extending into the main bronchus less than 2 cm distal to the carina but without involvement of the carina, or a tumor of any size with atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis involving the entire lung. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Lung cancer with invasion of the mediastinum, heart, great vessels, trachea, esophagus, vertebral body or carina, or presence of separate tumor nodules within a same lobe, or the presence of a malignant pleural effusion. Although most pleural effusions associated with lung cancer are due to tumor, there are a few patients in whom multiple cytopathologic examinations of the pleural fluid are negative for tumor. In these cases, the fluid is non-bloody and is not an exudate. Such patients may be further evaluated with videothoracoscopy and direct pleural biopsy. When these elements and clinical judgment dictate that the effusion is not related to the tumor, the effusion should be excluded as a staging element. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lung cancer in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lung cancer with no evidence of metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pN1 TNM Finding

value.value: Lung cancer with metastasis to ipsilateral peribronchial and/or ipsilateral hilar lymph nodes, including intrapulmonary nodes involved by direct extension of the primary tumor. (from CAP Lung Cancer Protocol--January 2005 Revision)

label.value: Lung Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lung cancer with metastasis to ipsilateral mediastinal and/or subcarinal lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Lung cancer with metastasis to contralateral mediastinal, contralateral hilar, ipsilateral or contralateral scalene, or supraclavicular lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)
